00:40.540 --> 00:51.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Wisconsin Republican
Paul Ryan became the 54th
speaker of the House of
Representatives

00:51.184 --> 00:56.423 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
today. He's 45 years old, and
was the party's vice
presidential nominee in 2012.
Now he

00:56.423 --> 01:00.193 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
faces perhaps his
biggest test yet.

01:00.193 --> 01:06.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MAN: Mr. Speaker, the
speaker-elect, Paul D. Ryan of
the state of Wisconsin.

01:06.466 --> 01:09.403 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

01:09.403 --> 01:15.208 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The bipartisan
cheers, handshakes and hugs all
made clear the new speaker is

01:15.208 --> 01:20.147 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
popular with Republicans and
Democrats. And after taking the
gavel from Democratic Leader

01:20.147 --> 01:23.650 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Nancy Pelosi, Ryan
called for healing.

01:23.650 --> 01:29.823 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REP. PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker
of the House: The House is
broken. We're not solving
problems.

01:29.823 --> 01:36.997 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're adding to them. And I am
not interested in laying blame.
We are not settling scores.

01:36.997 --> 01:39.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We are wiping the slate clean.

01:39.800 --> 01:46.506 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: That drew a standing
ovation, and Ryan went on,
pledging more transparency,

01:46.506 --> 01:51.211 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
something rebellious
conservatives in his own party
and Democrats alike have
demanded.

01:51.211 --> 01:56.683 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
REP. PAUL RYAN: We need to let
every member contribute, not
once they have earned their

01:56.683 --> 02:03.890 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
stripes, but now. Let people
participate, and they might
change their mind. A neglected

02:03.890 --> 02:10.864 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
minority will gum up the works.
A respected minority will work
in good faith.

02:10.864 --> 02:16.103 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The nine-term
veteran, who until today chaired
the tax-writing Ways and Means

02:16.103 --> 02:22.175 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
panel, said he wants committees
to take the lead in drafting all
major legislation.

02:22.175 --> 02:25.278 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Ryan ultimately agreed to run
after demanding unified party
backing.

02:25.278 --> 02:28.348 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
WOMAN: Ryan.

02:28.348 --> 02:34.621 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Today, he came
close, winning 236 of the 245
Republican votes cast. The

02:34.621 --> 02:39.259 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
nine opposing him were
conservatives who had helped
force out Speaker John Boehner.

02:39.259 --> 02:45.732 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, Boehner bade his own
teary farewell, claiming credit
for ending earmarks and passing

02:45.732 --> 02:50.303 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a final two-year budget. His
last day in Congress is
Saturday.

02:50.303 --> 02:54.674 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
REP. JOHN BOEHNER (R-OH), Former
Speaker of the House: I leave
with no regrets, no burdens.

02:54.674 --> 03:00.347 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If anything, I leave the way I
started, just a regular guy,
humbled by the chance to do

03:00.347 --> 03:02.816 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a big job.

03:02.816 --> 03:12.559 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's what I'm most proud of.
I'm still just me. Real change
takes time. Yes, freedom makes

03:12.559 --> 03:19.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
all things possible. But
patience is what makes all
things real. So, believe in the

03:19.766 --> 03:24.971 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
long, slow struggle. Believe in
this country's ability to meet
her challenges and to lead

03:24.971 --> 03:27.541 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the world.

03:27.541 --> 03:33.447 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Later, the
quarter-century congressman
listened as Pelosi and Ryan
saluted his service,

03:33.447 --> 03:38.351 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and then he slipped out
the back of the chamber.

03:38.351 --> 03:43.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Ryan's first major challenge
will be passing spending bills
to flesh out the two-year budget

03:43.090 --> 03:47.160 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
deal that passed the House
yesterday. The deadline is early
December.

03:47.160 --> 03:51.932 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The commanders of
the U.S. and Chinese navies met
face-to-face today

03:51.932 --> 03:57.571 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
