in the South China Sea. U.S.
officials said they agreed

03:57.571 --> 04:04.511 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to follow existing protocols to
avoid clashes. On Tuesday, a
U.S. warship sailed within 12

04:04.511 --> 04:09.749 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
nautical miles of a
Chinese-built island in a
disputed area. The U.S.
maintains the area

04:09.749 --> 04:14.588 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is international waters. China
warned today against any repeat.

04:14.588 --> 04:20.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: In Vienna, Austria,
talks on the war in Syria are
getting under way, with
uncertain

04:20.627 --> 04:26.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
prospects. Secretary of State
John Kerry joined envoys from
nearly 20 nations today,
including,

04:26.233 --> 04:31.805 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
for the first time, a
representative from Iran. Rebel
groups were not invited.

04:31.805 --> 04:35.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, a Syrian human rights
group reported Russian
airstrikes have killed 600,
nearly

04:35.642 --> 04:38.145 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a third of them civilians.

04:38.145 --> 04:42.749 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, in Moscow, the Russian
Foreign Ministry rejected that
claim.

04:42.749 --> 04:47.621 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARIA ZAKHAROVA, Russian Foreign
Ministry (through translator): I
want to stress that

04:47.621 --> 04:52.259 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
such insinuations, whoever they
are coming from and whoever
shares them, they have nothing

04:52.259 --> 04:57.097 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to do with reality. We see them
as a part of that propaganda
campaign to distort Russian

04:57.097 --> 05:00.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
military actions in comparison
to what we can honestly call
failed efforts of the U.S.-led

05:00.867 --> 05:03.737 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
anti-Islamic State coalition.

05:03.737 --> 05:09.376 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The Russians say
their strikes are targeting
Islamic State and other jihadist

05:09.376 --> 05:13.146 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
groups. The U.S. says, in fact,
the targets have mostly been
rebels fighting the Assad

05:13.146 --> 05:15.015 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
government.

05:15.015 --> 05:19.786 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Israeli forces
shot and killed two Palestinians
today in the West Bank city

05:19.786 --> 05:26.059 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of Hebron. The Israelis said
both tried to stab soldiers. The
incidents led to clashes

05:26.059 --> 05:31.097 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Hebron between Palestinian
youths and Israeli forces. It
was another sign that a surge of

05:31.097 --> 05:34.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
violence in Jerusalem
is now spreading.

05:34.100 --> 05:40.040 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: A U.N. committee on
international aviation standards
has rejected a ban on shipping

05:40.040 --> 05:46.112 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rechargeable batteries on
passenger planes. That's despite
evidence they're a fire hazard.

05:46.112 --> 05:52.052 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was widely reported today
that the committee voted 11-7
against a ban. The U.S., along

05:52.052 --> 05:55.622 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
with pilots and plane
manufacturers, favored the
prohibition. The battery
industry argued

05:55.622 --> 05:57.724 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
against it.

05:57.724 --> 06:02.162 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In economic news,
Deutsche Bank announced big cuts
to its work force

06:02.162 --> 06:09.102 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in eliminating 35,000 jobs,
mostly by selling some of its
businesses. That follows heavy

06:09.102 --> 06:14.074 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
losses in the third quarter.
Germany's largest lender has had
to pay heavy fines and legal

06:14.074 --> 06:18.044 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
settlements over rigging a
benchmark interest rate.

06:18.044 --> 06:24.718 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And U.S. growth hit
the skids in the third quarter.
It came in at 1.5 percent,

06:24.718 --> 06:29.322 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
less than half the number for
the second quarter. That didn't
do much for the mood on Wall
Street.

06:29.322 --> 06:36.529 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
lost 23 points to close below
17756. The Nasdaq fell 21
points,

06:36.529 --> 06:41.134 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and the S&amp;P 500 slipped a point.

06:41.134 --> 06:47.207 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
China reverses its one-child
policy; true or false? -- we

06:47.207 --> 06:51.344 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
fact check the Republican
debate; the search for migrant
survivors off the coast of
Greece,

06:51.344 --> 06:55.982 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and much more.

06:55.982 --> 07:07.327 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now to a
massive shift in China.

07:07.327 --> 07:12.065 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Earlier today, its ruling
Communist Party announced a turn
from its
more-than-three-decades-old

07:12.065 --> 07:16.269 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
restriction on the number of
children couples can have.

07:16.269 --> 07:20.807 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lucy Watson of Independent
Television News reports from
Beijing.

07:20.807 --> 07:27.614 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LUCY WATSON: China's one-child
policy is changing, and the end
of its brutal intrusion into
family

07:27.614 --> 07:34.054 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
life is nigh. Couples will now
be allowed two children. For
more than 35 years, the

07:34.054 --> 07:38.792 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
one-child rule has been
enforced by punishing families.

07:38.792 --> 07:44.197 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BAI XIO LING, Mother: (through
translator): When they fired me
for having a second baby,

07:44.197 --> 07:50.970 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we were almost too poor to feed
ourselves. We were beaten up for
campaigning for my daughter's

07:50.970 --> 07:57.811 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
life. But nobody
would listen to us.

07:57.811 --> 08:05.118 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LUCY WATSON: Bai Xio Ling dared
to have two daughters, Li Bing
(ph) and Li Xue, two sisters

08:05.118 --> 08:10.390 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
eight years apart. One exists
according to Chinese law. The
other doesn't, just because

08:10.390 --> 08:13.159 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
she came second.

08:13.159 --> 08:20.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LI XUE, China (through
translator): I was born in
China. I'm Chinese. But I have
no

08:20.867 --> 08:27.507 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
rights. I couldn't go to school.
I can't travel. I can't see a
doctor. Nothing in my life
works.

08:27.507 --> 08:34.214 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LUCY WATSON: It was in 1979 that
the legislation was introduced
by Deng Xiaoping to curb a

08:34.214 --> 08:39.352 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
then surging population and
avoid stifling economic growth.
Now a different demographic

08:39.352 --> 08:42.222 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
crisis looms.

08:42.222 --> 08:47.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DU PENG, Renmin University
(through translator): A labor
shortage and a rapidly aging
population

08:47.694 --> 08:51.865 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
caused by the policy undermine
economic growth. It's not always
good if the birthrate stays

08:51.865 --> 08:55.034 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
low. We need a more
balanced model.

08:55.034 --> 09:00.440 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LUCY WATSON: But it could be too
little too late in a country
where the rights to have

09:00.440 --> 09:03.943 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and raise a child are
still being manipulated.

09:03.943 --> 09:09.949 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Joining me now to
discuss the change is Mei Fong,
a Pulitzer Prize-winning

09:09.949 --> 09:14.487 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
journalist with over a decade of
experience covering Asia. She's
the author of the upcoming

09:14.487 --> 09:18.825 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
book "One Child: The Story of
China's Most Radical
Experiment."

09:18.825 --> 09:21.828 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Mei Fong, welcome
to the program.

09:21.828 --> 09:26.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, just how significant a shift
in policy is this for China's
communist leadership?

09:26.900 --> 09:29.569 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MEI FONG, "One Child: The Story
of China's Most Radical
Experiment": Well, your segment

09:29.569 --> 09:34.240 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
mentioned too little too late,
and that's really kind of what
it is.

09:34.240 --> 09:40.547 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the past 15 years now, a lot
of experts of demographics,
economists, demographers,

09:40.547 --> 09:46.219 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have been asking for this change
to happen. They have all warned
of the aging tsunami

09:46.219 --> 09:51.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that's going to happen. They
have warned of the gender
imbalances. But the Chinese
government

09:51.090 --> 09:56.463 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has been very, very slow to
change it, so actually the
question is not why it happened

09:56.463 --> 09:59.699 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
now, but why has it taken
so long to happen.

09:59.699 --> 10:03.336 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, why do you
think they decided now? I mean,
we heard some of the

10:03.336 --> 10:07.841 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
reasons there, but what -- what
do you think has led them to do
this right now?

10:07.841 --> 10:14.180 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MEI FONG: Well, it's a looming
crisis that's affecting the
economic growth of the future.

10:14.180 --> 10:20.153 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Right now, there are about five
working adults to support one
retiree in China. That's a

10:20.153 --> 10:27.327 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
pretty good ratio. But in 20
years' time, that's going to be
1.6 working adults to one

10:27.327 --> 10:32.232 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
elderly retiree. That's a huge
difference. And there's not
going to be enough people

10:32.232 --> 10:37.904 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to pay in for all these pension
imbalances and support an aging
population that, if it

10:37.904 --> 10:43.343 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
were its own country, would be
the third largest country in the
world after China and India.

10:43.343 --> 10:48.548 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: How
representative, Mei Fong, is the
story we just saw of that
family? They

10:48.548 --> 10:52.552 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
had two daughters. And one of
the daughters is basically a
non-person.

10:52.552 --> 10:58.324 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MEI FONG: They call them
heihaizi, black children,
because they don't exist.
They're non-people.

10:58.324 --> 11:03.963 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are about, estimated,
between 13 to 15 million of
these children that -- not
necessarily

11:03.963 --> 11:07.534 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
children. Now some of them are
adults. But for all intents and
purposes, they just don't

11:07.534 --> 11:14.307 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
exist in China. They can't
register to buy a house. They
can't go to school.

11:14.307 --> 11:19.312 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That girl that she interviewed,
I spoke to her. Her name is Sno
(ph). She is 20 years

11:19.312 --> 11:22.849 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
old. She's never been to school.
She can't even get so much as a
library card, because

11:22.849 --> 11:25.818 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
she has no registration rights.

11:25.818 --> 11:29.489 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Will the
government now make some sort of
attempt to redress that because

11:29.489 --> 11:31.658 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
they're changing the policy?

11:31.658 --> 11:36.029 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MEI FONG: It's really difficult,
because one of the big issues
that they fear is places

11:36.029 --> 11:38.665 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
like Beijing and Shanghai.
Beijing and Shanghai already
have something like 18 to 20
million

11:38.665 --> 11:41.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
people, city residents.

11:41.267 --> 11:48.341 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They are very afraid of changing
the household registration to
enable everybody to have those

11:48.341 --> 11:52.278 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rights, because they fear this
flood of people and there won't
be enough resources to service

11:52.278 --> 11:56.149 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
20 million people in the city.

11:56.149 --> 12:00.820 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So it's going to be very thorny.
A lot of people have actually
been suing to have these

12:00.820 --> 12:05.425 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rights. This girl, for example,
she has been spending the last
three to four years fruitlessly

12:05.425 --> 12:08.628 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
trying to sue the government to
give her those rights, which
legally she's entitled to, but

12:08.628 --> 12:11.497 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
she's still not able to get it.

12:11.497 --> 12:16.302 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What difference
is it thought this is going to
make in China's -- in the

12:16.302 --> 12:19.005 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
decisions families make? I mean,
is it thought that many families
will now decide to have

12:19.005 --> 12:20.406 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a second child?

